English compulsory learning


As globalization progresses, English is becoming the universal stardard language in multiple spheres.
Some people argue that everyone should learn English due to globalization. Others, however, believe that we should not be forced to learn english as it violates personal freedom. This essay will examine both perspectives and illustarate the reasons why I bielieve we should have the right to choice any language we would like to learn.



Violating personal freedom means infringing on an individual's basic rights to liberty, movement, privacy, and self-determination,

